The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 New Delhi, Nov. 28: The government today issued the second tranche of special bonds worth Rs 5,000 crore to oil marketing companies to help them offset losses due to high international crude prices. The first tranche of the same amount was issued in October. Indian Oil Corporation, including IBP, have been issued bonds worth Rs 2,838 crore, BPCL Rs 1,135 crore and HPCL Rs 1,027 crore.

 London/Calcutta, Nov. 28: CSN today started discussions with pension fund trustees of Corus, as more bankers expressed support for the Brazilian firms bid, while Tata Steel remained tight-lipped on matching the counter offer.

 New Delhi, Nov. 28: ONGC Videsh, along with Italys Eni Spa, Spains Repsol YPF and Norways Norsk Hydro, has won oil exploration blocks in Brazil. The country is offering blocks in 14 regions spread over 100,000 square kilometres.

 Mumbai, Nov. 28: The Reserve Bank (RBI) has brought in an amendment today to the Foreign Exchange Management Act (Fema) to further liberalise the provisions on current account transactions. 

 New Delhi, Nov. 28: India and Pakistan have rejected the gas import price worked out by a consultant appointed by Iran as part of the over $7-billion tri-nation pipeline project.




